    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - TRANSFER CASES - REMOVE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>REMOVE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="0">
            <title>PREPARATION</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">After removing transfer case from vehicle, clean exterior prior to disassembly. Care
                    should be taken to prevent water from entering assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove drain plug at bottom of case and drain lubricant.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">A clean working area is essential. It is important to prevent foreign material from
                    entering assembly during repairs.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position transfer case in a suitable holding fixture or horizontally on a table with
                    upper front input and lower front output facing upward or forward.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
